page.title: 15COUNTRY RANGERS
page.content: The country rangers (Bob and Keith) came from Poulton Hall.we found out that they cover 120 acres of land,including Spital Dam. The rangers jobs are to cut the grass,protect the wildlife,build new footpaths and keep all the weeds from growing too tall. The rangers cover south of Spital Dam,east of Bromborough Village,north of Dibbinsdale Road and Poulton Hall.The part the rangers cover is a place of scientific interest.This means it is an interesting place to scientists. The rangers see foxes,voles, water shrews and lots of other animals. They have some new footpaths that have been built by Manpower Services. In the area are Himalyan Balsam and Japanese Knotweed.
